    "title": "Guided Practice: Categorizing COSHH and BS 7671",
    "objective": "Categorize industry documents into statutory and non-statutory groups using the 'Law vs Guidance' rule.",
    "retrievalTextLines": [
      "Recall the worked example: The EAWR is a law (Statutory), while the On-Site Guide is technical advice (Non-statutory).",
      "Statutory regulations are Acts of Parliament that carry the force of law.",
      "Non-statutory regulations are technical standards that show how to comply with those laws.",
      "Consider two more documents: COSHH (Control of Substances Hazardous to Health) and BS 7671 (The Wiring Regulations)."
    ],
    "questionText": "Identify which of these two—COSHH or BS 7671—is the Statutory Regulation and explain why based on its legal status.",
    "answerGuidance": [
      "COSHH is the Statutory Regulation because it is a legally binding law/Act of Parliament, whereas BS 7671 is a non-statutory technical standard."
    ],
    "hint": "Ask yourself: Which one is a law passed by Parliament, and which one is a technical manual for installers?"
  },
